Let's get started.

...but the reward is achieving something to be proud of. Something that moves you forward in life. 

There are no shortcuts - starting will be tough, sticking to it even tougher...

Achieve was designed to help you start and stick with your goals.

But starting something new can be hard.

You can acomplish so much...

Welcome to Achieve.

i

What's your goal?

Exercise - Lose weight so I look better and feel healthier.

Cook - Meal prep more so I eat out less.

Hobby - Get better at drawing people.

Social media - Spend less time on instagram. 

My Goal

Great.


Now, think about what you need to do in the next week to move closer to your goal.


If you’re not sure, that’s alright!


This is less about being perfect and more about getting started.

A task in Achieve is something you can acomplish in one sitting. It should be something small that you can do in a few hours or less.


What tasks can you work on this week?

Curtain



Curtain

Peer support is a key strategy to help you stick to your goals. Here’s how it works.


  • We’ll match you with a peer.
  • You and them meet up weekly for 15 to 30 minutes. We’ll initially help with speaking prompts to break the ice and promote task discussion.


Meeting someone new takes courage, but together you'll be stronger.

Try it out first

Add peer support to schedule.

(no real people, just practice.)

Exercise more and lose weight.
